deck: Vol 1
description:
Created by Coheed & Cambria lead singer Claudio Sanchez, In Keeping Secrets of Silent Earth: 3 is the third chapter (following Year of the Black Rainbow and The Second Stage Turbine) of the overarching Amory Wars storyline detailing the album of the same name.  Ten years have passed since Claudio's parents passed away in The Second Stage Turbine, and Jesse Kilgannon (aka The Prize Fighter Inferno) is taking on Supreme Tri-Mage Wilhelm Ryan's Red Army in revenge of Coheed & Cambria's death.  As Claudio emerges from the planet Shylos Ten, Ryan and the reinstated General Mayo Deftinwolf sense that Claudio is still alive and may be the undoing of their plans for domination of the Keywork and Heaven's Fence in general.  Claudio is found by the Prise Ambellina, and with the help of the IRO-bot Sizer, Claudio finds himself on a mission to stop Wilhelm Ryan's tyranny.
 
Collected in The Amory Wars: In Keeping Secrets of Silent Earth: 3.
name: The Amory Wars: In Keeping Secrets of Silent Earth: 3

deck: World Watch was designed to be an answer to Warren Ellis' Authority, but with more over the top explicit sex, violence and real politics. In a tongue in cheek gesture, the second issue of the series contained a note from the publisher, stating that Chuck Austen had been fired from the book, despite the fact that he owned and published it himself.
description: Worldwatch is the imaginary comics version of “Exposing Myself”, the tell-all memoirs of Dena Warchawski, a.k.a. War Woman, frontrunner of the Worldwatch superteam organized by professor turned unintentional superhero Doc Gulliver under the initial sponsorship of the United Nations. The story tells how team members’ private affairs and dishonesty led to the team’s self-destruction.
name: WorldWatch

deck: After exposure to a meteor rock, a young man named Gabriel experiences his world turning upside down.  That's the very abridged version of what happens in the first issue of A-10 Comics' The Damaged.
description: Centuries ago, humans were different. They possessed abilities that would seem miraculous to modern man. Somehow, that all changed, and human beings became the normal descendants of apes that populate the world today. That is, until an asteroid from a dead planet collides with the Earth, unlocking the secrets of the human DNA code with its impact. Can one man be responsible, and are his motives aimed at benefiting all of mankind? Or is he out to destroy those who are even now discovering these once-hidden secrets? Discover who The Damaged really are in this incredible new ongoing series chronicling a struggle that will either save us from ourselves, or rip the world apart!
name: Damaged
